  <h2 class="section-title">Do <span>You Know</span></h2>
  <div class="facts-myths-container">
    <div class="box facts">
      <h3>Facts</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <i>✔️</i> The process is relatively painless, with only a slight prick
          during needle insertion.
        </li>
        <li>
          <i>✔️</i> A healthy body replenishes lost blood within 48 hours with
          no long-term effects.
        </li>
        <li>
          <i>✔️</i> All equipment used is sterile and single-use, ensuring no
          risk of infection.
        </li>
        <li>
          <i>✔️</i> Blood banks need a constant supply for emergencies and
          chronic conditions.
        </li>
        <li>
          <i>✔️</i> Vegetarians have enough nutrients, including iron, to
          maintain healthy hemoglobin levels.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="vs-circle">VS</div>

    <div class="box myths">
      <h3>Myths</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><i>❌</i> Donating blood is painful.</li>
        <li><i>❌</i> Donating blood weakens the donor.</li>
        <li><i>❌</i> You can catch diseases like HIV from donating.</li>
        <li><i>❌</i> Blood donation is only needed during emergencies.</li>
        <li><i>❌</i> Vegetarians cannot donate blood.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
